# Handoff-first (Grok ‚Üî Cursor loop)

When **LOOP.bat** or `tools/agent-loop.ps1` is running, autonomous cycles use `Docs/grok-handoff/`.

## On every session

1. Read `Docs/grok-handoff/STATUS.md` ‚Äî respect **State:**
2. If `GROK_DONE`, `CURSOR_PENDING`, or `CURSOR_WORKING` ‚Üí implement `CURSOR_TASKS.md` using `grok-response.md`
3. If `GROK_PENDING` / tasks in `GROK_TASKS.md` ‚Üí wait for loop to run Grok, or run `.\tools\agent-handoff.ps1 -RunGrok`
4. After shipping ‚Üí set **CURSOR_SHIPPED**; loop runs sync/commit/release

## State machine

`IDLE` ‚Üí `GROK_PENDING` ‚Üí `GROK_WORKING` ‚Üí `GROK_DONE` ‚Üí `CURSOR_PENDING` ‚Üí `CURSOR_WORKING` ‚Üí `CURSOR_SHIPPED` ‚Üí `SHIPPED`

## Rules

- Questie `wotlkItemDB.lua` wins for item IDs
- Grok does **not** edit `.lua`; Cursor implements
- Full autonomy: `Docs/AUTONOMOUS_LOOP.md`
- Manual one-shot still works: `agent-handoff.ps1 -RunGrok -NotifyCursor`
